{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"Cupid enrichment op: LLM ticket-digest extractor + digest schema.\n\n## Why\nSemantic overlap detection needs a compact, normalized per-ticket representation that\ncatches paraphrase (\"login broken\" vs \"users can't authenticate\") WITHOUT embeddings,\nkeeping rebar on its Anthropic-only, no-heavy-ML grain. The Cupid pattern\n(arXiv:2308.10022) uses an LLM as a one-time feature extractor. DERISKED: the recall\nexperiment (see epic experiment comment) showed digest-BM25F retrieves 8/8 heavy\nparaphrases at rank 1 (recall@20 = 1.0); the digest is the load-bearing artifact for the\nwhole feature.\n\n## What\nA new LLM operation `rebar.llm.enrich(ticket_id)` returning a validated dedup-digest\nwrapper, plus its output schema and prompt. It is a **structured single-turn** op:\nassemble the ticket's canonical text -> load the prompt ->\n`RunRequest(mode=\"structured\", output_schema=\"ticket_digest\", execution_mode=\"single_turn\")`\n-> `get_runner(cfg, override=runner).run(req)` (the runner validates the structured\nresponse against the `ticket_digest` schema via `finalize_outcome`/`validate_structured`)\n-> the op post-processes the proposition count and returns the wrapper.\n\nModeled on the structured single-turn pattern in\n`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/passes.py::pass1_chunk` (which builds\n`RunRequest(mode=\"structured\", execution_mode=\"single_turn\")`) â€” **NOT** on\n`src/rebar/llm/completion.py` (that is a *gate* op that resolves a read-root and delegates\nverdict production to the workflow engine; it contains no `RunRequest`), and **NOT** on\n`operations.py::review_ticket` (which uses `mode=\"findings\"`/`execution_mode=\"agentic\"`,\nthe opposite of what we want). Because `enrich` is single-turn with no file/repo tools it\ndoes **NOT** need `gate_source.resolve_gate_handle` / `gate_read_root` or snapshot\nmaterialization; it builds cfg via `LLMConfig.from_env(repo_root=...)` (or an explicit\n`config=`), assembles the ticket text, and runs.\n\nThe digest schema (`ticket_digest`):\n`{problem_keywords: string[], component_or_area: string, key_entities: string[], propositions: string[]}`;\n`propositions` = 2-6 atomic problem/repro statements; logs/stack-traces/code are discarded\nby the prompt. The payload is deterministic (no timestamps/uuids) so the stored record is\nstable modulo LLM wording.\n\n### Instructions assembly (query context â€” resolves \"which fields, what format\")\nThe op assembles the single-turn `instructions` from the ticket's canonical text â€”\n**title + description + comments** â€” via the canonical normalizer\n`rebar._engine_support.gates._ticket_text(ticket)` (the same title+desc+comments\nnormalizer S1/S2 reuse for the content hash), rendered as plain text. No graph, no file\ncontents, no logs are included; the prompt itself instructs the model to discard any\nlogs/stack-traces/code that appear in the body.\n\n## Return shape & processing order (resolves the two-layer output shape)\n1. Build the `RunRequest` and call `get_runner(cfg, override=runner).run(req)`. The runner\n   selects the pydantic model via `contracts.response_model_for(\"ticket_digest\")`, and\n   `findings.finalize_outcome(..., mode=\"structured\", output_schema=\"ticket_digest\")`\n   validates the model's structured response against the `ticket_digest` JSON schema. The\n   runner thus returns a dict already valid against `ticket_digest` (its four fields).\n2. The op then post-processes the `propositions` list ONLY: if `len > overlap_propositions_max`,\n   truncate to max; if `len < overlap_propositions_min`, keep them all and set\n   `low_proposition_count=True`; it never raises on count.\n3. The op returns the wrapper\n   `{\"digest\": <ticket_digest dict, four fields>, \"low_proposition_count\": bool}`.\n   `low_proposition_count` lives on the op's RETURN object only â€” it is never a fifth field\n   of the persisted `ticket_digest`.\n\n## Error contract (resolves AC \"clean error, no partial write\")\n- Malformed / absent structured output (the model returned no parseable structured object)\n  surfaces as `rebar.llm.errors.StructuredOutputError` (subclass of `LLMRunnerError` ->\n  `LLMError`) raised inside `finalize_outcome`. The op does NOT catch-and-partial-write â€” it\n  propagates, so no record is ever persisted from a bad parse. A shape violation (valid JSON,\n  wrong shape) raises `FindingsError` from `validate_structured`. The op defines NO new\n  exception type (it reuses the framework's).\n- Absent LLM (no `[agents]` extra / no API key) raises `LLMUnavailableError` (subclass of\n  `LLMError`) cleanly via the runner/config path.\n\n## Config-bound threading (resolves the zero-arg-builder gap)\nThe proposition bound is NOT enforced through the `register_contract` schema builder (the\nzero-arg `Callable[[], type]` cannot see config). Instead: (a) the prompt instructs the\nmodel to emit MIN..MAX propositions, and (b) the op post-validates the parsed count\n(truncate to max if more; keep + flag `low_proposition_count` if fewer; never raise). The\nMIN/MAX bounds are LLM-feature tunables on `LLMConfig` (`[tool.rebar.llm]`, env\n`REBAR_LLM_OVERLAP_PROPOSITIONS_MIN` / `REBAR_LLM_OVERLAP_PROPOSITIONS_MAX`, read in\n`LLMConfig.from_env` via the `_llm_int` helper) â€” `_config_schema.py` reserves the `llm.*`\nlayer, so these must NOT go on `VerifyConfig`.\n\n## Scope (exact edit targets)\n- `src/rebar/llm/config.py`: add module constants `DEFAULT_OVERLAP_PROPOSITIONS_MIN = 2` /\n  `DEFAULT_OVERLAP_PROPOSITIONS_MAX = 6`, dataclass fields\n  `LLMConfig.overlap_propositions_min` / `overlap_propositions_max`, and two `_llm_int(...)`\n  lines in `from_env` (env `REBAR_LLM_OVERLAP_PROPOSITIONS_MIN/MAX`, file keys\n  `overlap_propositions_min/max`).\n- New op module `src/rebar/llm/enrich.py` defining\n  `enrich(ticket_id, *, repo_root=None, config=None, runner=None)` and the zero-arg pydantic\n  builder `ticket_digest_response_model()`.\n- Export: add `from rebar.llm.enrich import enrich` to `src/rebar/llm/__init__.py` and add\n  `\"enrich\"` to the `# operations` group of its `__all__` (NOT `src/rebar/__init__.py`; the\n  core package must not import `rebar.llm`).\n- Prompt `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/enrich.md`, front-matter `schema_version: 1`,\n  `execution_mode: single_turn`, `outputs: ticket_digest`, and NO `category: review` (so it\n  is not indexed/selected as a reviewer â€” `reviewers/index.json` lists only\n  `category==\"review\"`). The valid `execution_mode` enum is `single_turn|agentic`\n  (`prompting/prompts.py:74`); `1-TURN` is invalid.\n- Output schema `src/rebar/schemas/ticket_digest.schema.json` (all four fields required;\n  `problem_keywords`/`key_entities`/`propositions` = arrays of non-empty strings;\n  `component_or_area` a non-empty string; `propositions` `minItems: 1`). WIRE IT: in\n  `src/rebar/schemas/__init__.py` add `TICKET_DIGEST = \"ticket_digest\"`, register\n  `OUTPUT_SCHEMAS[\"enrich\"] = TICKET_DIGEST`, and add `TICKET_DIGEST` to `__all__` â€” this\n  satisfies `tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_coverage.py::test_every_schema_file_is_wired`\n  (every schema file must appear in `OUTPUT_SCHEMAS.values() | exempt`). The synthetic\n  `\"enrich\"` key has no CLI `--output` arm (like `\"verify_completion\"`), so the CLI-coverage\n  invariants do not drive it.\n- Contract registration + bootstrap: define the builder `ticket_digest_response_model()` in\n  `src/rebar/llm/enrich.py`, and register it at the BOTTOM of `src/rebar/llm/contracts.py`\n  with `register_contract(\"ticket_digest\", ticket_digest_response_model)` next to the two\n  built-ins (`review_result`, `completion_verdict`). `contracts.py` is imported\n  unconditionally at startup (via `rebar.llm.__init__`), guaranteeing registration before\n  `response_model_for(\"ticket_digest\")` is first called. Import the builder from `enrich.py`\n  at the bottom of `contracts.py`; if that would create an import cycle, define the builder\n  in `contracts.py` itself and import it into `enrich.py`.\n\n## Dependencies\nNone (leaf). S1/S2/S7 consume the op + the `ticket_digest` schema as sibling stories.\n\n## Testing\n- Unit `tests/unit/test_enrich.py` (all use `FakeRunner` with canned structured responses â€”\n  NO live LLM): `test_schema_valid` (wrapper's `digest` validates), `test_logs_excluded`\n  (stack-trace frames absent from the digest), `test_no_nondeterministic_fields`,\n  `test_propositions_bounded` (>max truncated to max; <min sets `low_proposition_count`, no\n  raise), `test_bad_json` (FakeRunner returns malformed/absent structured output ->\n  `StructuredOutputError`, and nothing is written), `test_absent_llm` (raises\n  `LLMUnavailableError`), and `test_enrich_exported` (`from rebar.llm import enrich` succeeds\n  AND `rebar.llm.contracts.response_model_for(\"ticket_digest\")` returns the ticket_digest\n  model, not the default findings model â€” covers the export + contract-registration Scope\n  items).\n- Quality fixture test `test_enrich_quality` â€” **fully offline, deterministic, no live\n  LLM**. Fixtures live at `tests/fixtures/enrich_quality/*.json`, >=6 files COMMITTED as\n  deliverables of this story, each shaped\n  `{\"ticket_id\": str, \"body\": str (one is a ~4000-token body), \"digest\": {<pre-generated ticket_digest, four fields, captured once from a real enrich run>}, \"gold\": [<expected entity/keyword strings>]}`.\n  The test loads each fixture's pre-generated `digest` (it does NOT call the LLM) and asserts\n  deterministic string-set membership: >=1 `gold` string appears (case-insensitive) in\n  `digest.key_entities` union `digest.problem_keywords`. The `digest` blocks are canned\n  real-model outputs, regenerated only when the prompt changes. Proving command:\n  `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_enrich.py -q` (self-contained; fixtures are committed so\n  it never needs a generation step first).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `rebar.llm.enrich(ticket_id)` returns `{digest, low_proposition_count}`, and the\n  `digest` field validates against the `ticket_digest` schema;\n  `pytest tests/unit/test_enrich.py::test_schema_valid`.\n- [ ] `from rebar.llm import enrich` succeeds and `contracts.response_model_for(\"ticket_digest\")`\n  returns the registered model (not the default findings model);\n  `pytest tests/unit/test_enrich.py::test_enrich_exported`.\n- [ ] Logs/stack-traces/code are excluded from the digest;\n  `pytest tests/unit/test_enrich.py::test_logs_excluded`.\n- [ ] The payload has no nondeterministic fields;\n  `pytest tests/unit/test_enrich.py::test_no_nondeterministic_fields`.\n- [ ] The `propositions` count is enforced in the op (>max truncate to max; <min keep + flag,\n  no raise); `pytest tests/unit/test_enrich.py::test_propositions_bounded`.\n- [ ] Malformed/absent structured output raises `StructuredOutputError` with no partial\n  write (`::test_bad_json`); absent-LLM raises `LLMUnavailableError` (`::test_absent_llm`).\n- [ ] The offline quality fixture test (>=6 committed labeled fixtures carrying pre-generated\n  digests) asserts >=1 gold entity/keyword appears in `key_entities` union\n  `problem_keywords` (deterministic string-set membership, no live LLM);\n  `pytest tests/unit/test_enrich.py::test_enrich_quality`."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783645766291589001,"uuid":"20acb0c4-a8c1-4299-9824-c3f2b8fa473f"}